CAPE TOWN - Five people will be appearing in court on Monday in connection with the Imizamo Yethu protests in Hout Bay.Two homes have been torched, while foreign-owned shops and a local ANC office have been vandalised recently.Community leaders also suspect the murder of a 19-year old man, whose body was discovered at the weekend is linked to the unrest.Police Minister Fikile Mbalula visited the informal settlement over the weekend. He's assured residents that more arrests are imminent.READ - Police minister welcomes peace deal in Hout BayMbalula is also promising he'll deploy more police officers to the area.eNCA